## Run the following command to install libvirt (Requires SUDO)

```bash
ansible-playbook -vvv main.yml -i "localhost" --connection="localhost" --extra-vars "state=present" -t="libvirt" -K
```

## Host Bridge Automation

When `state=present`, this role can  configures a NetworkManager bridge (`br0`) for libvirt host bridging.

Defaults are defined in [roles/libvirt/defaults/main.yml](roles/libvirt/defaults/main.yml):

- `libvirt_configure_host_bridge: true`
- `libvirt_bridge_name: br0`
- `libvirt_bridge_uplink_interface` (optional override)

Example override:

```bash
ansible-playbook -vvv main.yml -i "localhost," --connection="local" --extra-vars "state=present libvirt_configure_host_bridge=true libvirt_bridge_uplink_interface=enp4s0" -t="libvirt" -K
```